org.nerd4j.csv.reader

Class CSVReaderMetadata<Model>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.nerd4j.csv.reader.CSVReaderMetadata<Model>
  • Type Parameters:
    Model - type of the field mapping descriptor.

    public final class CSVReaderMetadata<Model>
extends Object
    Represents the meta-data used to tell a CSVReaderFactoryImpl how to build and configure the related CSVReaders.
    Author:
    Nerd4j Team

    • Constructor Detail

      • CSVReaderMetadata

        public CSVReaderMetadata(CSVParserMetadata parserMetadata,
                 CSVToModelBinderFactory<Model> modelBinderFactory,
                 CSVFieldMetadata<String,?>[] fieldConfigurations,
                 boolean readHeader,
                 boolean useColumnNames,
                 boolean acceptIncompleteRecords)
        Constructor with parameters.
        Parameters:
        parserMetadata - the parser meta-data to use.
        modelBinderFactory - the factory able to create CSVToModelBinders.
        fieldConfigurations - the configurations related to the single fields.
        readHeader - tells if the header should be read.
        useColumnNames - tells to use the column names in the header to perform column mapping.
        acceptIncompleteRecords - tells to accept CSV where not all records have the same number of fields.
